<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3238029>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Spockia tagala gen. & sp. nov. Roca-Cusachs & Jung. a, Dorsal habitus; b, ventral habitus; c–i, Male genitalia: c, caudal pygofore; d, lateral pygofore; e, dorsal pygofore; f, ventral pygofore; g, segment X (proctiger); h, paramere: dorsal, lateral and ventral; i, aedeagus, dorsal and ventral. Scale bar equals 1 mm. dpr, dorsoposterior rim; lpa, lateroposterior angle; pa, parandria vpr, ventroposterior rim; blcl, basolateral conjunctival lobe; mpp, median penial plates; v, vesica; pt, phalloteca." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3238029/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3238031>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. a, Peritreme and Evaporatorium; b, detail of male setose glandular patches, white arrow shows position." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3238031/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3238033>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Female genitalia of Spockia tagala gen. & sp. nov. Roca-Cusachs & Jung. a, spermatheca, Scale bar equals 0.25mm.; b, External female plates. Scale bar equals 0.5mm. aaf, anterior annular flange; cs, capsula seminalis; paf, posterior annular flange; gc, gonocoxites; la, laterotergites; va, vesicular area; iva, internal rod of vesicular area; dr, ductus receptaculi." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3238033/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

